    "comment": "Rationale: ABHD6 localizes to postsynaptic spines of glutamatergic neurons in adult mouse prefrontal cortex (Figure 5G-H). Localization of ABHD6 is juxtaposed (not overlapping) with presynaptic CB1-receptors which bind 2-AG, the lipid metabolized by ABHD6. Supplementary Figure 9 shows ABHD6 is mainly expressed glutamatergic neurons and to a lesser extent GABAergic interneurons and some astrocytes.\n\nPostsynaptic membrane annotation: ABHD6 is an integral membrane protein (active site faces cytoplasm).\n\n5/12/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Electron microscopy: C57BL/6 mice; adulte, cortical layers 4-5 (Fig 5)\nCell type and synapse type immunostaining: C57BL/6 mouse cortical sections (sup. Fig 9)",
